                incorporate uncertainty in their decisions and calculate their probabilistic outcomes of every action; this is called the <b>rational choice theory</b>.  
            
                <p></p>So, what does it mean to be rational?  It is decision-making behaviour which is guided by reasoning that certain behaviour would result in an expected outcome.  
                This leads to another assumption that game outcomes are controlled by the player’s decisions rather than by pure chance.  A player’s knowledge of a game and 
